<div class="pure-g">
    <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-4 small-hide"></div>
    <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-2 content-box">
        <div id="main-logo-container"><img src="images/OR-Logo.png"></div>
        <div class="head">
            <span class="green">OREGON</span>
            PROCUREMENT SEARCH
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-1-4 small-hide"></div>
</div>

<div class="pure-g">
    <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-7-24 small-hide"></div>
    <div class="pure-u-1 pure-u-md-10-24 content-box l-box">
        <form method="get" action="/search">
            <input type="text" name="kw" placeholder="Search...">
            <button type="submit" class="pure-button">Search OR Procurements</button>
        </form>
        <p class="tip">
            Example: landscape architecture<br>
        </p>

        <p>
            Are you an Oregon business owner? Do you want to do
            business with the government? Find out who's buying what
            you're selling.
        </p>

        <p>
        	<b>You can search for open procurement contracts with these agencies:</b>
        	<ul>
        		<li>The City of Beaverton</li>
        		<li>The City of Portland</li>
        		<li>The Port of Portland</li>
        		<li>Metro</li>
        		<li>Portland State University</li>
        		<li>Chemeketa Community College</li>
        		<li>The Portland Development Commission</li>
        		<li>The Oregon Department of Corrections</li>
        	</ul>
        </p>

        <p>
            Do you want instant updates on new contracts with any of these agencies?
        </p>

        <p>
            Right-click <a href="http://oregonprocurementsearch.com/rss">here</a> and
            copy this url, then add it to your RSS reader.
        </p>

        <p>
            Or, install an RSS reader app on your Android phone or
            iPhone and you can receive push notifications of ORPIN
            procurement opportunites on your phone.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="pure-g">
    <div class="pure-u-1 l-box">
        <div class="footnote">

            <div class="pages large-hide">
                <div class="head">Pages</div>
                <ul>
                    @Html.Partial("Pages-menu")
                </ul>
            </div>

            <p class="tip">
                Got questions?  Oh yes you do.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
